There is a science behind the practice of Eating Mindfully!

The quality of your digestion is affected by mind, environment, body, and emotions. So where you’re eating, what you’re watching while eating, your mental state can all affect your blood flow and in turn have an impact on your digestion process. 

When you are rested and mindful when eating, the parasympathetic system is active which is responsible for all the involuntary systems in your body while you are at rest including your heart rate, digestion, etc. Along with promoting better digestion, mindful eating also helps with weight management as it increases awareness of fullness and reduces unnecessary cravings. This practice also reduces cortisol levels a.k.a. Stress hormones in the body.

Here’s how you can start practicing mindful eating.

- Choose a time to have a meal by yourself when you can be fully present.

- Choose a quiet place to sit 

- After taking your first bite, put your food back down and rest your hands on your lap. 

- Sit and experience the taste on your tongue and the texture of the food in your mouth. 

- Once chewed and savored, swallow and begin again with another bite. Continue until you are full.
